-->Types of Shell
---------------------------------------------------
---/bin/sh(bourne shell), /bin/bash(bourne again shell), /bin/dash(Debian Almquist Shell), /bin/csh(c shell), /bin/ksh(korn shell),/bin/zsh(z shell)
---------------------------------------------------



------------------------
|    Applications      | ← User-level programs (e.g., browsers, editors, etc.)
|=========="===========|
|        Shell         | ← Interface between user and OS (CLI or GUI)
|======================|
|       Kernal         | ← Core part of the OS (manages resources and system calls)------>|   Process management, Memory management,Device management,File system handling,System calls   |
|======================|
|       Hardware       | ← Physical components (CPU, memory, I/O devices) --->  |  CPU, RAM,Disk drives,Network cards  |
------------------------



-----***----- How It All Works Together: -----***------
==============================================================================
A user runs a program from the shell.

The shell converts the request into system calls to the kernel.

The kernel accesses the necessary hardware resources to fulfill the request.

The result travels back up the layers to the user.
